24/05/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Croatia will start issuing new biometric passports on January 1st, local media reported Friday (May 22nd).
The government adopted the law on travel documents' amendments under which passports will contain fingerprints, facial biometrics and individual citizen ID numbers.
All public servants with diplomatic passports will have biometric data included in their documents earlier, as July 1st.
The related bill has already been sent to parliament for approval.
(Vjesnik, Javno, Croatian Times - 22/05/09)
